With all the scuttlebutt regarding coach and executive openings across the league seemingly focused on the New York Knicks and Golden State Warriors, it was the Detroit Pistons who swooped in and made the biggest organizational splash since the 2013-14 regular season ended. According to ESPN.com reporter Marc Stein's sources, Detroit owner Tom Gores has enticed Stan Van Gundy to leave the cozy confines of the broadcast booth to take over the Pistons both in the front office and on the bench. The $35 million is plenty of reason in itself for the outspoken Van Gundy to jump back into the fray, but the dual executive-coach offer must have set Detroit apart from other possible SVG suitors such as Golden State. To read Bradford Doolittle's full story on Stan Van Gundy's hiring in Detroit, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Bradford Doolittle Follow Archive Sports reporter, Kansas City Star, 2002-09 Writer, Baseball, Baseball Prospectus Co-author, Pro Basketball Prospectus Member, Baseball Writers Association of America Member, Professional Basketball Writers Association